<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-06T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-06T03:35:00-05:00" n="587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">791.003/77: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-06T12:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">March 6,
                                        1928—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 6—6
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>22. Department’s 18, March 5.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>(1)</label>
                            <item>My reference was meant to imply that our independent attitude
                                might be prejudiced with the Persians by an obvious cooperation in
                                treaty negotiations with only the British.</item>
                            <label>(2)</label>
                            <item>Belgium has now authorized its representative here to begin
                                negotiations.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>